counter.name: CacheHitCount
counter.desc:
Provides a count of the total number of times an attempt to access a bean from the cache succeeded.

The sum of the Cache Hit Count and Cache Miss Count may not add up to the cacheAccessCount in a running server because these metrics are retrieved using multiple calls and the counts could change between the calls.

counter.name: CacheMissCount
counter.desc:
Provides a count of the total number of times an attempt to access a bean from the cache failed.

The sum of the Cache Hit Count and Cache Miss Count may not add up to the cacheAccessCount in a running server because these metrics are retrieved using multiple calls and the counts could change between the calls.

counter.name: CacheAccessCount
counter.desc:
Provides a count of the total number of attempts to access a bean from the cache.

The sum of the Cache Hit Count and Cache Miss Count may not add up to the cacheAccessCount in a running server because these metrics are retrieved using multiple calls and the counts could change between the calls.

counter.name: CacheMissByTimeoutCount

counter.name: FreeHeap
counter.desc: The amount (in bytes) of Java heap memory that is currently free in the Virtual Machine.

counter.desc: The time at which the last garbage collection run started.

counter.desc: The number of garbage collection runs that have occurred since the Virtual Machine was started.

counter.name: HeapSizeCurrent
counter.desc: The current size (in bytes) of the JVM heap.

counter.name: Uptime
counter.desc: The number of milliseconds that the Virtual Machine has been running.

counter.name: UsedPhysicalMemory
counter.desc:
The amount (in bytes) of physical memory that is currently being used on the host computer.

The value describes the memory that is being used by all processes on the computer, not just by the Virtual Machine.

counter.name: TotalGarbageCollectionTime
counter.desc: The number of milliseconds that the Virtual Machine has spent on all garbage collection runs since the VM was started.

counter.name: TotalNurserySize
counter.desc:
The amount (in bytes) of memory that is currently allocated to the nursery.

The nursery is the area of the Java heap that the VM allocates to most objects. Instead of garbage collecting the entire heap, generational garbage collectors focus on the nursery. Because most objects die young, most of the time it is sufficient to garbage collect only the nursery and not the entire heap.

If you are not using a generational garbage collector, the nursery size is 0.

counter.desc: The amount (in bytes) of physical memory that is currently free on the host computer.

counter.name: HeapSizeMax

counter.name: LastGCEnd
counter.desc: The time at which the last garbage collection run ended.

counter.name: TotalPhysicalMemory
counter.desc:
The amount (in bytes) of physical memory on the host computer.

The value does not include memory that an operating makes available through swap space on a disk or other types of virtual memory.

counter.name: UsedHeap
counter.desc: The amount (in bytes) of Java heap memory that is currently being used by the Virtual Machine.

counter.name: HeapFreeCurrent
counter.desc: The current amount of memory (in bytes) that is available in the JVM heap.

counter.name: TotalHeap
counter.desc:
The amount (in bytes) of memory currently allocated to the Virtual Machine's Java heap.

This value, which is also known as the "heap size," may grow up to the specified maximum heap size.
